        <title>Methods of Learning Foregin Languages and My Materials</title>
        <link>https://kaseeia-hsu.github.io/p/methods-of-learning-foregin-languages-and-my-materials/</link>
        <pubDate>Mon, 29 Aug 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
        
        <guid>https://kaseeia-hsu.github.io/p/methods-of-learning-foregin-languages-and-my-materials/</guid>
        <description>&lt;img src="https://i.imgur.com/KC4iPov.jpg" alt="Featured image of post Methods of Learning Foregin Languages and My Materials" /&gt;&lt;h1 id=&#34;methods-of-learning-foregin-languages&#34;&gt;Methods of Learning Foregin Languages&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Having decent learning materials is definitely one of the most important, and also the first thing first to do when you start learning a new language,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But be wary of becoming one of those people who collects language learning material, though. Once you&amp;rsquo;ve worked your way through one complete grammar book,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s time to try your wings rather than going back to the beginning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And learning languages is not just about &amp;ldquo;remembering&amp;rdquo; all the time though its crucial to build your own vocabulary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While most people don&amp;rsquo;t do learning by going through grammar books, I find that using a good grammar book together with learning phrases and vocabulary really&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Puts things into proper perspective. There will be details that are over your head. Skip those things until they become relevant to what you are learning or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;have learned and focus on those things that are currently relevant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&#34;italian&#34;&gt;Italian&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;Ciao&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is what I use for my textbook.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;Litaliano secondo il metodo natura&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This book uses Natural-learning method so that learners could absord the language itself before having any background knowledge about it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Me personally love this method a lot and I&amp;rsquo;ll definitely recommend others to try it!:)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;Modern Italian Grammar - A Practical Guide&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A complete guide for grammars that you must know.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;Assimil italian with ease&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A great book to support your study.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assimil series are always best-known for their way of teaching European language though they&amp;rsquo;re expensive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&#34;german&#34;&gt;German&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;Deutsch Nach Der Naturmethode&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Natural-learning method for German&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;Deutsche Sprachlehre Fur Ausländer&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My first textbook for German.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;Modern GERMAN Grammar&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A complete guide for grammars that you must know.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&#34;latin&#34;&gt;Latin&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;A Primer of Ecclesiastical Latin&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I use it as my workbook, and the questions in it are quite interesting!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;Learn to Read Latin&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s the best and the most detailed text book that I&amp;rsquo;ve ever found.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After finishing this book, you would have the ability to read most of the Latin works by yourself.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;Lingua Latina per se Illustrata&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Natural Learning method for Latin.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&#34;tools&#34;&gt;Tools&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://github.com/language-transfer&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;Language Transfer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I don&amp;rsquo;t know if this works well since I barely have time to check it out!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But many people have recommened this; therefore, I believe it helps more or less&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://archive.org/details/italianpod/italianpod_0001dg.mp3&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;ItalianPod Archive&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wonderful material for Italian listening practice.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
        </item>
